The beach is characterized by high limestone cliffs along the entire coastal strip of the city. The city of Netanya is located in the central part of the Sharon Valley, about 30 km north of Tel Aviv and 56 km south of Haifa. It is famous for its clean beaches (9 beaches with a total length of 14 km) , modern recreational facilities and hotels. Netanya stretches along the sea and the length of the beach area surpasses other cities in Israel, including Tel Aviv. In the past, a major citrus center and one of the largest centers of the country's powerful diamond industry.